    vkd3d_vulkan_info, and the feature struct to the physical-device info
    chain. The R8_UINT case in the OMM index-type convert helper now
    checks index_type_uint8_features.indexTypeUint8 and returns false on
    missing support, dropping the BLAS build instead of handing the driver
    a VK_INDEX_TYPE_UINT8 it can't accept. OMM enablement is intentionally
    not gated on indexTypeUint8: R8_UINT OMM index buffers are rare, so
    per-build fail-soft is preferred over disabling OMM device-wide on
    stacks without UINT8 support.

