commit 5d4459fcda095654ca22a67c6141c3ae622ea8db
Author: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 8 19:35:13 2026 -0700

    vkd3d: Track AS kind as 4-state enum, gate BLP postbuild on it.

    Each cached AS view carries a vkd3d_rtas_kind (UNKNOWN, TLAS,
    NON_TLAS, MUTATED) updated by vkd3d_va_map_place_acceleration_structure
    via an atomic CAS loop:
      UNKNOWN -> TLAS | NON_TLAS  on first known-kind place
      TLAS | NON_TLAS -> MUTATED  on cross-kind reuse at the same VA
      MUTATED                     terminal
    place(UNKNOWN) is a no-op and never overwrites an established kind.

    The SERIALIZATION-info writer gates the BLP slot per kind:
      TLAS                emit BLP query
      NON_TLAS            zero-fill (spec-conformant, VUID-12425)
      UNKNOWN | MUTATED   config-controlled (default: emit BLP, opt-in
                          zero-fill via VKD3D_CONFIG=zero_fill_blp)

    VUID-12425 forbids BLP queries against an AS not built as
    TYPE_TOP_LEVEL_KHR. D3D12 permits EmitPostBuildInfo to be recorded
    before the corresponding build, with submission order resolving the
    temporal ambiguity, so the cache cannot be guaranteed accurate at CPU
    record time. NV is observed to tolerate BLP against non-TLAS benignly
    (returns 0); the zero_fill_blp flag lets portability-sensitive runs
    opt out of the VUID violation entirely.

    emit_postbuild_info and CopyRaytracingAccelerationStructure fall back
    to place_acceleration_structure (with UNKNOWN) when try_read_rtas
    misses, then ERR if placement also fails.

    Signed-off-by: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
