Author: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
Date:   Fri May 8 23:06:21 2026 -0700

    vkd3d: Merge OMM postbuild writer into AS writer.

    Once OMM-Array became a VkAccelerationStructureKHR built via the v2
    KHR path, vkd3d_opacity_micromap_write_postbuild_info and
    vkd3d_acceleration_structure_write_postbuild_info were near-identical:
    same vkCmdWriteAccelerationStructuresPropertiesKHR call on same-typed
    handles, same query type per InfoType, differing only in the
    SERIALIZATION NumBottomLevelPointers second query (which OMM doesn't
    have). Add a bool is_micromap parameter to the AS-side writer and fold
    that one branch in; remove the OMM-side writer and its now-unused
    prototype.

    OMM postbuild now also honors the rayTracingMaintenance1 gate for
    CURRENT_SIZE the same way regular AS already did. Pre-merge OMM
    ignored the gate and would call vkCmdWriteAccelerationStructuresPropertiesKHR
    with VK_QUERY_TYPE_ACCELERATION_STRUCTURE_SIZE_KHR -- an m1-only query
    type -- on devices that exposed OMM tier without m1.

    The OMM SERIALIZATION NumBottomLevelPointers slot was previously
    uninitialized: the OMM-side writer's stride was sizeof(uint64_t) while
    the outer caller advanced by 2 * sizeof(uint64_t) per entry, leaving
    the second uint64 untouched. The merged writer's fillbuffer(0) for
    the OMM SERIALIZATION case picks up that second slot, restoring the
    16-byte D3D12 SERIALIZATION layout per entry.

    The CURRENT_SIZE-without-m1 branch is split out so its FIXME names the
    missing extension instead of falling into "Unsupported InfoType"; the
    SERIALIZATION-without-m1 FIXME gets the same parenthetical.

    Signed-off-by: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
