commit 58c375948bf5c9ea8169d4b49545376b941a4eb4
Author: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
Date:   Wed May 6 10:21:56 2026 -0700

    vkd3d: Skip OMM-linkage handle resolution on prebuild sizing queries.

    vkGetAccelerationStructureBuildSizesKHR doesn't dereference any input
    VAs -- it sizes from geometry counts and types only -- and apps
    commonly fill the OMM linkage descriptor once with their planned
    layout and reuse it for both the prebuild sizing query and the later
    build. That means a non-zero OMM-Array VA can legitimately be present
    during prebuild before the buffer is committed. Today, conversion
    unconditionally resolves that VA against the va_map and the prebuild
    path emits a flood of "Failed to query opacity micromap for VA ..."
    ERRs.

    Lift the OMM-Array handle resolution out of
    vkd3d_acceleration_structure_convert_opacity_micromap into a separate
    post-pass, vkd3d_acceleration_structure_resolve_omm_va_maps. Conversion
    is now pure struct shaping and leaves omm_triangles_info->micromap
    as VK_NULL_HANDLE (memset by the caller). Build paths run the
    post-pass after convert_inputs and propagate resolution failures
    the same way they always have. Prebuild paths skip the post-pass;
    the size query is fine with VK_NULL_HANDLE in the pNext chain.

    Signed-off-by: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
---
 libs/vkd3d/command.c          |  4 ++++
 libs/vkd3d/opacity_micromap.c | 44 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----------
 libs/vkd3d/vkd3d_private.h    |  3 +++
