Author: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 27 17:29:33 2026 -0700

    vkd3d: Route OMM copy through vkd3d_acceleration_structure_copy.

    With KHR-OMM living in VkAccelerationStructureKHR and the va_map's
    dual AS / OMM out-params already collapsed to a single handle plus
    kind, vkd3d_opacity_micromap_copy and vkd3d_acceleration_structure
    _copy were 95% identical: same vkCmdCopyAccelerationStructureKHR
    call on same-typed handles, differing only in which kind to pass to
    vkd3d_va_map_place_acceleration_structure for the destination view,
    plus a duplicate convert_copy_mode static helper.

    Add a bool rtas_is_omm parameter to vkd3d_acceleration_structure
    _copy and thread it through to the va_map place call. The OMM-side
    copy function and its duplicate convert_copy_mode go away; the
    dispatcher in CopyRaytracingAccelerationStructure calls the AS-side
    function for both kinds, passing is_micromap from the va_map read.
    The fallback placement path passes false to the place call: without
    a cached view to read the kind from, the fallback cannot know
    whether the source is OMM or AS, so an OMM source hitting this path
    will have its dst classified as AS-side. The behavior is
    pre-existing.

    Tighten the info-struct init while we're here: memset up front,
    early return on convert_copy_mode failure, and let the explicit
    field assignments overwrite only the non-zero slots. The ERR
    message on a failed dst placement is now kind-aware.

    Signed-off-by: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
