Author: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 27 12:47:30 2026 -0700

    vkd3d: Switch shared OMM helpers to KHR-spelled enums and types.

    A handful of OMM helpers were left with EXT-spelled identifiers when
    the rest of the backend was switched to KHR. They compile because the
    EXT enum values and typedefs in Vulkan-Headers alias to their KHR
    counterparts, but the source-level spelling is inconsistent with the
    rest of the OMM code paths.

    Switch the residual identifiers to their canonical KHR spellings:

      - d3d12_format_to_vk return type:
        VkOpacityMicromapFormatEXT -> VkOpacityMicromapFormatKHR
      - Format enumerators:
        VK_OPACITY_MICROMAP_FORMAT_{2,4}_STATE_EXT -> ..._KHR
      - Pipeline-flag bit:
        VK_PIPELINE_CREATE_2_RAY_TRACING_OPACITY_MICROMAP_BIT_EXT ->
        VK_PIPELINE_CREATE_2_RAY_TRACING_OPACITY_MICROMAP_BIT_KHR

    Behavior unchanged: each renamed symbol's KHR form is the canonical
    Vulkan-Headers definition and the EXT form is the typedef alias, so
    the assignment lowers to the same value either way.

    Signed-off-by: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
