commit b8346e5a9f7e39693fe04f96710b735086a860d6
Author: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 27 11:40:45 2026 -0700

    vkd3d: Remove EXT backend for OMM array builds.

    Reverses the EXT side of "Add KHR backend for OMM array builds".
    Drops d3d12_command_list_allocate_omm_build_info_ext,
    d3d12_command_list_build_raytracing_opacity_micromap_array_ext,
    d3d12_build_flags_to_vk_ext, and
    vkd3d_opacity_micromap_convert_inputs_ext. The remaining KHR-side
    helpers drop their _khr suffix as the only surviving variants:

      - d3d12_command_list_allocate_omm_build_info_khr ->
        d3d12_command_list_allocate_omm_build_info
      - d3d12_command_list_build_raytracing_opacity_micromap_array_khr +
        the dispatcher -> merged into single
        d3d12_command_list_build_raytracing_opacity_micromap_array
        (now void instead of bool)
      - d3d12_build_flags_to_vk_khr -> d3d12_build_flags_to_vk
      - vkd3d_opacity_micromap_convert_inputs_khr ->
        vkd3d_opacity_micromap_convert_inputs

    Two further EXT-side dispatches collapse:

      - d3d12_command_list_fixup_rtas_batch's omm_build_infos.ext
        usage-count fixup loop is removed; the KHR-side bodies (geometry-
        pNext fixup and usage-count fixup) become unconditional inside
        the if (supports_opacity_micromap) gate.
      - d3d12_command_list_flush_rtas_batch's vkCmdBuildMicromapsEXT
        call is removed. In KHR mode OMM-Array builds dispatch as part
        of vkCmdBuildAccelerationStructuresKHR (OMM-Array is just an AS
        with type=OPACITY_MICROMAP_KHR), so the separate EXT dispatch
        is dead.

    With EXT removed, omm_build_info_count is now always paired with
    build_info_count (allocate_omm_build_info increments both), so the
    flush-time early-return condition simplifies to checking
    build_info_count alone, and the unconditional dispatch drops the
    now-tautological if-guard.

    Signed-off-by: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
