    vkd3d: Remove EXT-only OMM barrier and buffer bits.

    Reverses the OMM-KHR series's "Gate EXT-only OMM barrier and buffer
    bits to EXT mode" commit. Now that EXT is no longer enabled at device
    creation, the gating condition (supports_opacity_micromap &&
    !using_khr_opacity_micromap) can never be true - supports_opacity_micromap
    is set only when KHR is in use, in which case using_khr_opacity_micromap
    is also set. The EXT-only stage, access, and buffer-usage bits gated
    on this condition are dead code and removed here.

    Six sites:
      - vk_access_and_stage_flags_from_d3d12_resource_state, three
        branches (UAV state, RTAS state, NON_PIXEL_SHADER_RESOURCE state)
      - d3d12_command_list_BuildRaytracingAccelerationStructure, the
        type-change-flush memory barrier
      - vkd3d_create_buffer, the RTAS-storage buffer usage flags
      - vkd3d_memory_info_init, the RTAS-storage buffer usage flags

    Remaining VK_*_MICROMAP_*_BIT_EXT references inside
    vkd3d_opacity_micromap_emit_immediate_postbuild_info's EXT branch
    are also dead but live inside the OMM postbuild-info dispatcher;
    they're removed when that dispatcher's EXT backend is excised
    later in this series.

    Signed-off-by: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
