commit 3c3b1deb739e956f93794bfaa61fbc5fca10b66b
Author: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 27 10:28:16 2026 -0700

    vkd3d: Stop enabling VK_EXT_opacity_micromap.

    Stop requesting VK_EXT_opacity_micromap at device creation. EXT-only
    devices will no longer report OMM support; KHR-capable devices are
    unaffected since KHR was already preferred by the resolution block.

    Drop EXT_OPACITY_MICROMAP from optional_device_extensions, the
    EXT_opacity_micromap bool from vkd3d_vulkan_info, the EXT feature-
    struct chain prepend in vkd3d_physical_device_info_init, and the
    EXT TRACE block in vkd3d_trace_physical_device_features. Collapse
    the OMM-availability selection (the if-clear and the OR-with-EXT)
    so supports_opacity_micromap is now just using_khr_opacity_micromap.

    The EXT helper bodies in opacity_micromap.c remain in place as
    unreachable dead code so the codebase still compiles.

    Signed-off-by: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
