    vkd3d: Add KHR backend for OMM postbuild info.

    Extend vkd3d_opacity_micromap_write_postbuild_info to dispatch on
    using_khr_opacity_micromap. KHR mode submits the query via
    vkCmdWriteAccelerationStructuresPropertiesKHR with AS-compacted-size,
    AS-size, and AS-serialization-size query types, reusing the
    VKD3D_QUERY_TYPE_INDEX_RT_* indices already used by the AS postbuild
    path. EXT continues to use vkCmdWriteMicromapsPropertiesEXT and its
    OMM-specific query indices.

    KHR gains native CURRENT_SIZE support since the AS query covers it;
    the EXT-only "we cannot query in Vulkan, just clear to 0" fallback
    behavior stays in the EXT branch unchanged.

    vkd3d_opacity_micromap_emit_immediate_postbuild_info also dispatches
    its pre-query barrier on using_khr_opacity_micromap. KHR mode uses
    VK_PIPELINE_STAGE_2_ACCELERATION_STRUCTURE_BUILD_BIT_KHR with
    VK_ACCESS_2_ACCELERATION_STRUCTURE_WRITE/READ_BIT_KHR because the
    OMM array is built and consumed as a regular AS; the EXT branch
    keeps the existing micromap-stage / MICROMAP_*_BIT_EXT barrier.

    The KHR path remains dormant per the EXT-prefer-until-final-MR rule.
