commit 63dd155065f877f8446aadd9056e2a7c77e79841
Author: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 25 21:44:13 2026 -0700

    vkd3d: Add KHR backend for OMM array builds.

    Introduce unions vkd3d_omm_build_info and vkd3d_omm_usage_info as
    EXT/KHR pointer overlays for OMM-array build descriptors and per-entry
    usage arrays, and split the convert and allocate helpers into _ext and
    _khr variants. KHR builds an OMM array as a regular AS with type
    OPACITY_MICROMAP_KHR, geometry type MICROMAP_KHR, and a chained
    VkAccelerationStructureGeometryMicromapDataKHR carrying usage counts
    and triangle data; EXT continues to use vkCmdBuildMicromapsEXT directly.

    The dispatcher and the fixup pass are reorganized around
    using_khr_opacity_micromap: KHR mode re-resolves the new
    geometry_info->pNext linkage and the KHR pUsageCounts; EXT mode
    re-resolves the EXT pUsageCounts and the existing triangles.pNext
    for OMM_TRIANGLES. range_ptrs[i] is set to NULL for MICROMAP_KHR
    entries per VUID-vkCmdBuildAccelerationStructuresKHR-ppBuildRangeInfos-11544.

    The KHR path is plumbed but dormant: using_khr_opacity_micromap is
    force-cleared during physical-device init, so EXT remains the only
    active backend. Removing the force-clear activates KHR.
