Author: Christopher Dannemiller <cdannemiller@nvidia.com>
Date:   Sun May 17 22:20:33 2026 -0700

    vkd3d: Detect VK_KHR_opacity_micromap, unify OMM check.

    Add KHR_opacity_micromap to the optional device extension list and
    record the result on vkd3d_vulkan_info. Split the OMM feature struct
    on vkd3d_physical_device_info into EXT and KHR variants, and add
    supports_opacity_micromap (a unified availability gate) plus
    using_khr_opacity_micromap (a backend discriminator).

    Callers that ask "is OMM available?" -- d3d12_device_supports_ray_tracing_tier_1_2,
    the DXR 1.2 tier promotion, the shader-extension wire-up -- go through
    supports_opacity_micromap. Callers that emit MICROMAP-typed barriers,
    pipeline stages, or buffer usage flags stay on opacity_micromap_features_ext
    directly: VK_PIPELINE_STAGE_2_MICROMAP_BUILD_BIT_EXT,
    VK_ACCESS_2_MICROMAP_*_BIT_EXT, and VK_BUFFER_USAGE_MICROMAP_STORAGE_BIT_EXT
    are EXT-typed in the headers with no KHR equivalent today, so there is
    no clean abstraction point. Those sites flip to the unified gate if and
    when KHR promotes the flags.

    Probe both feature bits via vkGetPhysicalDeviceFeatures2 so devices
    exposing both extensions can be discriminated. EXT is preferred for now
    via a one-line dormancy clamp that zeros opacity_micromap_features_khr.micromap
    after the query; flipping the preference to KHR is a one-line removal.

    Minor nit cleanups in review by Hans-Kristian.
    Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>
