Author: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>
Date:   Wed May 13 15:02:41 2026 +0200

    vkd3d: Add some diagnostics and workarounds for broken table VA.

    Elden Ring seems to hit some rather unfortunate edge cases where it
    passes in UINT64_MAX VA for descriptor table in some rare cases which is obviously
    completely broken, but by sheer luck it happens to be robust on native.
    The subsequent commit demonstrates various aspects of this insanity.

    There is no perfect solution here since we don't control page table
    layouts and descriptor heap robustness does not apply to plain table
    pointers unless we deliberately slow everything down by applying it to
    *every* resource access, not just descriptor indexing.

    The easiest fix is to just ignore these calls which fixes the game.
    We can deliberate on more hardcore robustness solutions if required.

    More diagnostics are added to be able to detect these cases going
    forward.

    Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>
