    vkd3d_create_acceleration_structure_view through the v2 entry;
    otherwise fall back to v1. This is the path KHR_OMM needs --
    OPACITY_MICROMAP-typed acceleration structures must be created via
    the v2 entry.

    On the v2 path, declare addressFlags. FULLY_BOUND: AS storage
    buffers are dedicated non-sparse device-local allocations, so every
    page in the declared range is memory-backed. STORAGE_BUFFER_USAGE:
    vkd3d-proton always sets VK_BUFFER_USAGE_STORAGE_BUFFER_BIT on
    D3D12 buffers, so the AS range has known storage-buffer usage.
    TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER_USAGE: same logic, conditional on
    EXT_transform_feedback to match the buffer-create gate.

    The view path's "buffer == AS" sanity FIXME is preserved. On v2 the
    spec guarantees the returned address equals addressRange.address, so
    the check is tautological but cheap. On v1 it still catches driver
    divergence for the GENERIC AS type vkd3d-proton uses.
