Author: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>
Date:   Fri Apr 17 17:23:43 2026 +0200

    vkd3d: Fix shader interface key for quirks above 32-bit.

    Ridiculous ...

    Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>
---
 libs/vkd3d/device.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/libs/vkd3d/device.c b/libs/vkd3d/device.c
index e1840e61..b501e692 100644
--- a/libs/vkd3d/device.c
+++ b/libs/vkd3d/device.c
@@ -10275,15 +10275,15 @@ static void vkd3d_compute_shader_interface_key(struct d3d12_device *device)
         key = hash_fnv1_iterate_u32(key, device->bindless_state.descriptor_buffer_sampler_size);
     }

-    key = hash_fnv1_iterate_u32(key, quirk_info->global_quirks);
-    key = hash_fnv1_iterate_u32(key, quirk_info->default_quirks);
+    key = hash_fnv1_iterate_u64(key, quirk_info->global_quirks);
+    key = hash_fnv1_iterate_u64(key, quirk_info->default_quirks);
     key = hash_fnv1_iterate_u32(key, quirk_info->num_entry_points);
     /* If apps attempt to use the same shader cache with different executables, we might end up with different
      * quirk tables due to app workarounds, so hash that too. */
     for (i = 0; i < quirk_info->num_entry_points; i++)
     {
         key = hash_fnv1_iterate_u64(key, quirk_info->entry_points[i].shader_hash);
-        key = hash_fnv1_iterate_u32(key, quirk_info->entry_points[i].quirks);
+        key = hash_fnv1_iterate_u64(key, quirk_info->entry_points[i].quirks);
         key = hash_fnv1_iterate_string(key, quirk_info->entry_points[i].entry ? quirk_info->entry_points[i].entry : "");
     }

commit dd78b4ff658526944c92a1e3360a1b3c808546f2
Author: Daniel Barrientos Anariba <69573860+danielbanariba@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 17 05:34:12 2026 -0600

    vkd3d: Implicitly bind RTPSO root signature for DispatchRays when none is set (#2940)

    Some DXR applications (e.g. RT64/sm64rt) call DispatchRays without
    explicitly calling SetComputeRootSignature beforehand, relying on the
    RTPSO's embedded global root signature. Native D3D12 drivers handle
    this implicitly.

    Previously, vkd3d-proton would fail to find a compatible pipeline
    variant in this scenario because:

    1. The degenerate variant (pipelines[0], created with NULL root
       signature as a fallback) would match the NULL bound root signature,
       but its pipeline handle is VK_NULL_HANDLE, so it cannot be used.

    2. The loop would break after finding this degenerate match, never
       reaching the real variant with a valid pipeline.

    This commit fixes both issues:

    - Skip degenerate variants with NULL pipeline handles instead of
      breaking the search loop.

    - When no compatible variant is found and the bound root signature is
      NULL or empty, fall back to the first variant with a valid pipeline
      and implicitly bind its global root signature. This ensures
      descriptor state is correctly initialized for the ray dispatch.

    Tested with sm64rt (Super Mario 64 RT64 path tracer) on NVIDIA
    RTX 3090 Ti, where this fix enables fully functional DXR path tracing
    that was previously producing black frames due to every DispatchRays
    call being silently dropped.

    Co-authored-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>
