    vkd3d: Avoid large FP value turning into INF when clearing.

    We're supposed to adhere to RTZ here, which means finite values will
    never create INF in smaller FP formats.

    Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>
---
